      • setWeight

        public void setWeight(double weight)
        Sets the weight of the edge Default width is provided in the following format For weights less than 4 the width is 1 pixel For weights less than 7 the width is 3 pixel For weights of other values greater than or equal to 7 the width is 5 pixel
        Parameters:

      • setWeight

        public void setWeight(AbstractVertex source,
             AbstractVertex destination,
             java.lang.String random)
        Sets a Random value between 0 and 9 to the weight attribute of the edge Syntax: A.createEdge(B, "randWeight"); Default width is provided in the following format For weights less than 4 the width is 1 pixel For weights less than 7 the width is 3 pixel For weights of other values greater than or equal to 7 the width is 5 pixel
        Parameters:
        weight - is the string "randWeight"
        source - contains the source Vertex
        source - contains the destination Vertex
        random - contains the String value "randWeight" later transformed in random double between 0.0-9.0
